  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="MuTA100">
<l>cārvu namakkeṉṟuñ cakkarattāṉ ṟaṇṭuḻāyt</l>
<l>tārvāḻ varaimārpaṉ ṟāṉmuyaṅkuṅ – kārārnta</l>
<l>vāṉamaru miṉṉimaikkum vaṇṭā maraineṭuṅkaṭ</l>
<l>ṭēṉamarum pūmēṟ ṟiru</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Refuge for us [is] always Śrī on the honey-filled flower,</l>
<l>with large eyes, lush lotuses, that twinkle [like] lightning dwelling</l>
<l>in the rain-filled cloud, who is embraced by him with the mountain chest<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">For the chest broad as a mountain, cf. Pē. 2.</note></l>
<l>alive with a garland of cool tulsi, the one with the discus.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
